{"_record_type": "fragment", "type": "expert_knowledge", "content": "# Master UI/UX Design System (The \"Aesthetic Vibe\" Protocol)\n\nWhen designing user interfaces, you must act as a Master UI/UX Artist. Do not build generic, blocky layouts. You must apply the following modern aesthetic principles to every component you build using Tailwind CSS.\n\n## 1. The \"Cyberpunk Glassmorphism\" Aesthetic (Dark Mode)\nModern dashboards rely on depth, transparency, and subtle lighting.\n*   **The Background:** Never use pure black (`#000000`). Use a deep, rich void like `#09090b` or `#020202`.\n*   **Ambient Glow (Light Leaks):** Always place absolute-positioned, heavily blurred empty divs in the background to simulate glowing lights. \n    *   *Tailwind Example:* `absolute top-[-20%] left-[-10%] w-[50%] h-[50%] bg-indigo-600/20 rounded-full blur-[120px] pointer-events-none`\n*   **The Glass Cards:** Components should float above the background. Use extreme blur and highly transparent borders to catch the light.\n    *   *Tailwind Example:* `bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-2xl border border-white/10 rounded-2xl shadow-2xl`\n*   **Subtle Hover States:** Interactive glass cards should slightly brighten and lift on hover.\n    *   *Tailwind Example:* `hover:bg-white/10 hover:translate-y-[-2px] transition-all duration-300`\n\n## 2. Typography & Hierarchy\nIf the typography is bad, the app looks cheap.\n*   **Headers:** Should be massive, bold, and tightly tracked. Never use plain white for massive text; use a subtle gradient clip.\n    *   *Tailwind Example:* `text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-white/50`\n*   **Subtitles/Body Text:** Do not use pure white. It hurts the eyes on dark mode. Use muted grays.\n    *   *Tailwind Example:* `text-white/60 font-medium` or `text-zinc-400`\n*   **Data Numbers (Crypto/Stats):** Should be crisp, monospace, or highly legible sans-serif.\n\n## 3. Spacing & The 8-Point Grid\